body:
For our division of Applications Development Center, we have an exciting opportunity for Recruiters willing to learn and develop their skills in IT recruitment. 
Does Java, .Net, PHP, QA and Mobile sound familiar to you? Than this is your place!
Your role will be to perform end-to-end recruitment and selection processes for various IT projects.

Key responsibilities:
•	You will evaluate applicants by discussing job requirements and applicant qualifications with managers; 
•	You’ll perform active search throughout the main recruitment channels as well as identifying new ones;
•	You’ll interview applicants on a consistent set of qualifications and compare their qualifications to the job requirements;
•	You will assess the project needs and you’ll build a suitable recruitment strategy;
•	You will refer applicants to the hiring managers in the organization, making hiring recommendations when appropriate;
•	You will work closely with the Development, Management and Support teams to deliver high quality recruitment services to our customers.

Requirements:
•	Bachelor or Master Degree in Psychology or Human Resources;
•	2+ years of professional experience in actively recruiting technical profiles (Software Developers, QA Engineers, Software Architects, Support Engineers, etc.);
•	3+ years of experience in HR/Recruitment;
•	Fluency in English and/or other European language is a must.

Ideal profile:
•	Ability to openly present her/his own ideas;
•	Independent and highly self-motivated with a strong customer focus;
•	Able to work both independently and as part of a team;
•	Willing and able to be part of international projects and initiatives;
•	Action and results orientated, ability to manage multiple priorities is also expected;
•	He/she should also have strong analytical skills, good organization skills and attention to details.
